Peru Stocks: Candente, Credicorp, Intergroup, Southern Copper

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-08-23T20:35:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/peru-stocks-candente-credicorp-intergroup-southern-copper.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rose 0.5 percent to 19,488.45. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 1.1 percent to 2,555.88.  Banking stocks surged after U.S. shares gained on optimism
the  Federal Reserve  will act to spur growth, said Leoncio Altamirano, a trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Scotiabank Peru SA (SCOTIAC1)  (SCOTIAC1 PE), the local unit of
 Canada ’s third-largest bank, rose 3.9 percent to 54 soles.
 Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
holding company, gained 3.3 percent to $92.  Intergroup Financial
Services Corp. (IFS)  , the owner of Peru’s fourth-largest bank
Interbank, climbed 2.6 percent to $23.80.  Banco Continental SA (CONTINC1) 
(CONTINC1 PE), the local unit of  Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA, rose 1.7 percent to 5.90 soles.  Zinc and copper miners gained after the metals advanced in
New York and  London .  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian zinc
exploration company, rose 6.7 percent to 16 cents.  Candente
Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, gained
4.6 percent to $1.14.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s
biggest copper producer, rose 1 percent to $30.10.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  